The paper deals with probabilistic automata and their verification using logical and behavioral equivalences. This falls under the category of formal methods and verification, which is covered by cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures for efficient model checking, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of probabilistic automata in artificial intelligence and software engineering, which are covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
